  "texts": [
    "However, avoiding the errors during inference time is challenging for neural models, because they lack in 7.",
    "factual evidence that can assist the models to judge the correctness of predictions.",
    "Furthermore, even if the models are equipped with knowledge, there exists a mismatch between knowledge and entity prediction that discourages models from properly detecting and correcting the errors.",
    "For example, the definition of \"NF-kappa B\" as \"an ubiquitous, inducible, nuclear transcriptional activator\" does not explicitly indicate that the type is \"protein\".",
    "To resolve the aforementioned challenge, we aim to propose a post-hoc verification framework that identifies errors from existing NER methods and revises them into more faithful predictions."
  ],
